SUMMARY:Mayor039\\\;s Neighborhood University Saturday Session  Florida-Fr
 iendly Landscaping
LOCATION:Hanna Avenue City Center 2555 East Hanna Avenue Tampa \, FL 33610
  United States
DESCRIPTION:From cold snaps to droughts\, Tampa landscapes have been throu
 gh it all. Ready to bounce back stronger? Our next Mayors Neighborhood Uni
 versity Saturday Session will show you how to create a yard that thrives i
 n our climate. Join our Florida-Friendly LandscapingTM workshop Your Best 
 Tampa Garden Starts Here\, from 9 a.m. until noon on Saturday\, May 16 at 
 the City Center at Hanna Avenue (2555 East Hanna Avenue). Learn from certi
 fied experts about smart design\, plant choices\, and soil care. Get the t
 ools you need to transform your outdoor space into a beautiful\, resilient
 \, and water-wise oasis. Featured experts include:  Lynn Barber\, Florida 
 Friendly LandscapingTM Agent\, UFIFAS Extension Hillsborough County  Anita
  Camacho of Little Red Wagon Native Plant Nursery and founder of the Tampa
  Bay Butterfly Association  Julia Palaschak Water Conservation and Efficie
 ncy Team Leader for the City of Tampa Water Department REGISTER HERE (http
 s:forms.cloud.microsoftPagesResponsePage.aspx?idcwOdjZFctEWQWxL-kYy2KPXOnK
