SUMMARY:Virtual Artful Connections
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Want a break from your day to de-stress and enjoy artwork? The
  Virtual Artful Connections is an art-viewing and discussion program focus
 ed on mental well-being and stress reduction. Join us on Zoom for an hour-
 long experience which includes: A relaxation exercise A question of the da
 y A facilitated discussion about one piece of artwork that is currently on
  display at the Tampa Museum of Art Space is limited\, and advanced regist
 ration is required. An email will be sent with the Zoom link once a ticket
  is ordered Sessions Available  130\, 227\, 327\, 424\, 529 This event is 
 held online via Zoom  Claim your ticket for the link! \n\nPermalink: https
 ://www.tampa.gov/node/180321
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/180321
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:c95c7565-cb76-465a-9fac-7e22022c07a8
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260525T002336Z
DTSTART:20260530T113000Z
DTEND:20260530T140000Z
SUMMARY:5K for Foster Kids
LOCATION:4810 N Himes Ave Tampa \, FL 33614 United States
DESCRIPTION:On May 30\, 2026\, the community will gather at Al Lopez Park 
 in Tampa for the 5K for Foster Kids\, a purposeful event dedicated to supp
 orting some of the most vulnerable members of the community. This morning 
 run serves as a vital fundraiser for the Childrens Network of Hillsborough
  County\\\; an organization committed to improving the lives of at-risk ch
 ildren and families through compassionate care and essential services. Par
 ticipants have the opportunity to transform their miles into meaningful ch
 ange\, with all proceeds directly benefiting programs that provide stabili
 ty and hope for children in the dependency system. The race itself is a pr
 ofessionally timed 5K managed by Victory Sports\, ensuring a high-quality 
 experience for both competitive runners and casual walkers. The course tak
 es full advantage of the scenic\, shaded paths within Al Lopez Park\, offe
 ring a beautiful backdrop for a Saturday morning of fitness and philanthro
 py. With chip timing in place\, every participant will receive an accurate
  assessment of their performance as they cross the finish line\, making it
  a great event for those looking to set a personal record or simply enjoy 
 a healthy outing for a great cause. To celebrate the efforts of the partic
 ipants\, an awards ceremony will follow the completion of the race. Recogn
 ition will be given to the top three overall male and female finishers\, a
 s well as the top three performers in various age groups\, ensuring that r
 unners of all stages of life have a chance to be honored for their achieve
 ment. Whether you are aiming for a podium finish or participating to show 
 your support for foster care awareness\, the 5K for Foster Kids promises a
  morning of community spirit\, athleticism\, and heartfelt impact. \n\nPer
 malink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/190291
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/190291
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:080c221e-4bce-44a4-9378-6ea688686793
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260525T002336Z
DTSTART:20260530T140000Z
DTEND:20260530T153000Z
SUMMARY:Ybor City Walking Tour
LOCATION:1600 E 8th Avenue Tampa \, FL 33605 United States
DESCRIPTION:Ybor City began as a cigar-manufacturing town and grew into on
 e of Tampas most distinctive historic districts. On this guided walking to
 ur\, guests will hear how cigar makers\, factory workers\, immigrant famil
 ies\, business owners\, and social clubs helped shape the neighborhood tha
 t became known around the world for hand-rolled cigars. Led by a History C
 enter-trained docent\, the 90-minute tour explores Ybor Citys brick street
 s\, landmark buildings\, and 7th Avenue corridor while connecting the neig
 hborhoods cigar industry to the people and places that shaped daily life i
 n Ybor City. Along the way\, guests will learn why Ybor City developed its
  own identity within Tampa and why so many of its historic buildings remai
 n important today. The tour begins at Parque Amigos de Jos Mart (Friends o
 f Jos Mart Park)\, 1303 E. Eighth Ave.\, Tampa\, FL 33605. Participants wi
 ll walk approximately one mile along public sidewalks and brick streets. C
 omfortable shoes and weather-appropriate clothing are recommended. Guests 
 may also want to bring bottled water. Advance tickets are required\, and s
 pace is limited to 25 guests. History Center members save 20 on walking to
 ur tickets by signing in before checkout. WALKING TOUR TICKETS Best parkin
 g options Centro Ybor Garage: 1500 E. 5th Ave. (https:maps.app.goo.glA8p5m
 SKrQCsebGJ68) (Access from N. 15th St or N 16th St) Ybor Lot 5: 1812 N. 19
 th St. (https:maps.app.goo.gljNEpFSuD2xFaySnY6) (Access from N. 18th St. o
 r N. 19th St.) Ybor Lot 3: 1701 N. 19th St. (https:maps.app.goo.glykuk8x3f
 dFTuE72i8) (Access from N. 19th St. or N. 20th St.) Click here (https:www.
 tampa.govparkingprogramsgarages-and-lots) for the full list of parking gar
 ages and lots owned by the City of Tampa. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa
 .gov/node/190441
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/190441
END:VEVENT
